## Ideal Customer Profile

**Question:** Describe your ICP. What industry / industries do they
belong to? What size, stage, geography? And how would you split your
leads into **P0 (must-have)**, **P1 (strong fit)**, and **P2 (worth
trying)** tiers? Be specific about what bumps a lead up or down a tier.

**Used by:** competitor_analysis · email_outreach · linkedin_outreach · signal_based_lead_outreach · icp_activity_tracker

**Example answer:**
> B2B SaaS, 20–200 employees, Seed to Series B, US + Western Europe.
> P0 = post-Series-A B2B SaaS with 5+ AEs, hiring RevOps, currently on
> HubSpot or Salesforce. P1 = same profile but earlier stage (Seed),
> or already on a modern CRM (Attio, Folk). P2 = adjacent verticals
> like dev-tools or fintech where pipeline hygiene still matters but
> the buying motion is different.

### Answer
<!-- agent writes here -->

---

## ICP Segments

**Question:** What categories do your ICP companies fall into? The
email_outreach workflow uses these to fill an `ICP Segment` column —
Claude assigns each enriched company to one of your segments. Format:
`Segment Name — short description (size / stage / industry signals
that define it)`.

**Used by:** email_outreach

**Example answer:**
> - **Scaling SaaS** — Series A/B B2B SaaS, 50–200 employees, 5+ AEs,
>   already on HubSpot or Salesforce.
> - **Early SaaS** — Seed-stage B2B SaaS, 10–50 employees, no RevOps
>   hire yet.
> - **AI-native startups** — any stage, building LLM-first products,
>   CRM is an afterthought.

### Answer
<!-- agent writes here -->

