## Right buyers

**Question:** Who are the right buyers inside a target company? One
sentence on each role — what they care about, what gets them to take a
meeting. Roles might be founder, head of sales, head of RevOps, head
of product, etc.

**Used by:** email_outreach · linkedin_outreach

**Example answer:**
> **Founder/CEO** at Seed-stage: cares about not hiring a RevOps
> person too early; takes meetings if we save them a hire.
> **Head of Sales** at Series A/B: cares about forecast accuracy and
> rep productivity; takes meetings if we have peer logos.
> **Head of RevOps**: cares about data hygiene and tool consolidation;
> takes meetings if we replace 2+ tools they already pay for.

### Answer
<!-- agent writes here -->

