## LinkedIn Post Relevance Filter

**Question:** When the workflow scrapes a person's recent LinkedIn
posts, what makes a post worth keeping vs. throwing out? Be specific —
vague criteria let too much noise through, or filter too hard and keep
nothing. Describe the kinds of posts that signal relevance, buying
intent, or a good conversation starter.

**Used by:** linkedin_outreach

**Example answer:**
> Keep posts that:
> - Mention pipeline hygiene, forecasting accuracy, or RevOps hiring
> - Complain about HubSpot / Salesforce / current CRM
> - Announce new sales hires (AE #2, first VP Sales, etc.)
> - Share an opinion or frustration about sales tooling
> Skip: thought-leadership generic content, motivational posts, posts
> that are pure reposts of someone else's content.

### Answer
<!-- agent writes here -->

